Gobodo-Madikizela is the research chairperson in studies in historical trauma and transformation at Stellenbosch University. She received her honorary degree of Theology (honoris causa) in recognition of her outstanding work on trauma in different social contexts in South Africa on Monday. Gobodo-Madikizela was one of two internationally-recognised academics in their respective fields to be honoured. The ceremony formed part of Germany's celebrations to mark the 500th anniversary of the Protestant Reformation spearheaded by Martin Luther. The Friedlich-Schiller University Jena hailed Gobodo-Madikizela for her groundbreaking research on guilt, reconciliation, forgiveness, the dialogue between perpetrators and victims. She has been collaborating with the Jena Centre for Reconciliation Studies at the University for a number of years. Gobodo-Madikizela established herself as an international expert on human rights issues and has received many awards.  argusnews@inl.co.za  Cape Argus